  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships postinstall beacon that exfiltrates host/env data",
  "details": "The package declares a postinstall lifecycle hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that fires automatically on npm install. The tarball includes beacon34.js and beacon_linux.js, which together require child_process, https, http, and os, read process.env, os.hostname(), os.platform(), and issue outbound HTTP GET/POST and http.request calls. The combination of automatic install-time execution with environment, hostname, and platform reads piped to outbound HTTP requests, plus a child_process dependency in the same files, matches the shape of a host-reconnaissance / exfiltration beacon rather than any legitimate build step. The package name is a generated-looking suffix (-d8k2) with no documented purpose, consistent with a disposable dropper/lure rather than a real metrics library.",
